'''''Golthar's Sky''''' was a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] conjured up by [[Sith sorcery/Legends|Sith magic]].

==History==
In [[3997 BBY]], it approached the [[Foerost Shipyards]] within [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] space, asking for hull repairs. The Foerost technicians were shocked at the immense size of the vessel, and asked them to hold position outside the yards while they sent out an inspection crew to determine what could be done.

It was all in vain, however, for the ship was actually a [[Mind trick/Legends#Force illusion|Force illusion]] created by [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic Qel-Droma's]] accomplice, the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] illusionist [[Aleema Keto]]. It was large enough to conceal several [[Supremacy-class attack ship|Krath attack ships]], with which Ulic used to [[Battle of Foerost (Great Sith War)|take the Republic by surprise]].

